The course takes place as an active learning seminar. The following topics will be addressed: research strategies, qualitative, quantitative, and mixed methods research; research ethics. In the seminars, specific master's theses to be performed will be analyzed.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the seminar is to prepare students for independent research. They get to know and critically read the specialized literature related to the topic. The main stages of doing and writing research (incl. developmental research) are introduced.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing this course the student
A student who has completed the course:
- is able to plan the research and its various stages,
- knows the main research strategies and methods used in pedagogy, their possibilities, and limitations,
-  in the creation of academic texts uses scientific language, including the rules of reference and citation,
- knows the terminology of didactics of informatics,
- is able to evaluate the correctness and limitations of the performed research,
- is able to carry out research with the assistance of a supervisor,
- can make an academic presentation.
